//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_diagonal" title=3D"Main diagonal">diagonal</a>=
 of a matrix denotes the number of each element that appears in a polyhedro=
n, whereas the non-diagonal of a matrix denotes the number of the column's =
elements that occur in or at the row's element. The regular dodecahedron ca=
